com.nokia.dempsy
Interface Adaptor

public interface Adaptor

An Adaptor is used to adapt data streams from external sources into Dempsy. Most Dempsy applictations contain at least one adaptor. The Adaptor needs to simply acquire the data meant to be processed by Dempsy and use the Dispatcher to send the message onward.

Method Summary
 void setDispatcher(Dispatcher dispatcher)
          This will be called by Dempsy to provide the Dispatcher to the Adaptor.
 void start()
          start will be called by Dempsy to tell the Adaptor that it can begin dispatching messages with the Dispatcher.
 void stop()
          This will be called by Dempsy in order to get the Adaptor to stop.
 

Method Detail

setDispatcher

void setDispatcher(Dispatcher dispatcher)
This will be called by Dempsy to provide the Dispatcher to the Adaptor. Any object that is the Dispatched will be sent to message processors.

start

void start()
start will be called by Dempsy to tell the Adaptor that it can begin dispatching messages with the Dispatcher. start() will always be called after Adpator.setDispatcher. This method is not expected to return until stop() is called from another thread.

stop

void stop()
This will be called by Dempsy in order to get the Adaptor to stop. Under normal circumstances the "start()" is still executing and the "stop()" should cause the "start()" to return. If it doesn't then Dempsy will most likely hang.
